{"chunkIndex":14,"totalChunks":17,"questionCount":50,"questions":[{"id":"so-7","question":"Put steps in order:\n1. Spread peanut butter\n2. Take out two slices of bread\n3. Put slices together\n4. Spread jelly","choices":["1, 2, 3, 4","2, 1, 4, 3","3, 2, 1, 4","4, 3, 2, 1"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Get bread → spread PB → spread jelly → combine.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Spread before getting.","2":"Combine before spreading.","3":"Backwards."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"pa-42","question":"What is the 8th term?\n2, 4, 6, 8, 10... ","choices":["12","14","16","18"],"answer":2,"explanation":"Even. 2n. 8th=16.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"6th.","1":"7th.","3":"9th."},"topicId":"patterns","topicName":"Number Patterns","sectionId":"quant"},{"id":"wp-44","question":"Box weights: 5kg, 7kg, 8kg, 4kg. Average?","choices":["4kg","6kg","7kg","8kg"],"answer":1,"explanation":"24/4=6.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Smallest.","2":"Wrong.","3":"Almost largest."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"tb-39","question":"The ______ team won ______ games in a row.","choices":["losing ... ten","winning ... ten","tired ... zero","new ... none"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Winning team → many wins in a row.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Losing doesn't win 10.","2":"Tired with zero wins doesn't make sense.","3":"None isn't a row."},"topicId":"two-blank","topicName":"Two-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"wp-3","question":"Shirt $40, 25% off. Sale price?","choices":["$10","$15","$25","$30"],"answer":3,"explanation":"$10 off. $30.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Discount.","1":"Wrong.","2":"Wrong."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"so-14","question":"Which sentence should come LAST in a paragraph?","choices":["For example, exercise improves heart health.","Exercise has many benefits.","In summary, exercise improves the body and mind.","Exercise also reduces stress."],"answer":2,"explanation":"\"In summary\" = conclusion.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Example fits middle.","1":"Topic sentence first.","3":"Detail middle."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"so-51","question":"Order to ride a bike to the park:\n1. Arrive at park\n2. Get on bike\n3. Pedal toward park\n4. Put on helmet","choices":["1, 2, 3, 4","4, 2, 3, 1","2, 3, 4, 1","3, 4, 1, 2"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Helmet → bike → pedal → arrive.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Arrive first.","2":"Helmet last.","3":"Pedal first."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"so-1","question":"Put these in chronological order:\n1. Growing up on a plantation\n2. Working on the Underground Railroad\n3. Escaping to the North\n4. Serving in the Civil War","choices":["1, 3, 2, 4","2, 1, 4, 3","3, 1, 2, 4","4, 3, 2, 1"],"answer":0,"explanation":"Born → escaped → worked → war.","wrongExplanations":{"1":"Out of order.","2":"Escape before born makes no sense.","3":"Backwards."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"so-47","question":"Which sentence fits the blank?\n\"My morning was busy. First, I made breakfast. ______. Finally, I caught the bus.\"","choices":["I love mornings.","Then, I packed my lunch and gathered my books.","Some kids skip breakfast.","I had eggs."],"answer":1,"explanation":"Need middle step.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Off-topic.","2":"Off-topic.","3":"Detail of breakfast."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"pa-30","question":"Rule: \"add the two before.\" 1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13, 21, ___","choices":["29","30","32","34"],"answer":3,"explanation":"13+21=34. (Fibonacci.)","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Wrong.","1":"Wrong.","2":"Wrong."},"topicId":"patterns","topicName":"Number Patterns","sectionId":"quant"},{"id":"tb-61","question":"The ______ salesperson ______ the customer to buy.","choices":["honest ... tricked","persuasive ... convinced","silent ... yelled","absent ... talked"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Persuasive → convinced.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Honest doesn't trick.","2":"Silent doesn't yell.","3":"Absent isn't talking."},"topicId":"two-blank","topicName":"Two-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"sb-49","question":"The clue was ______ and led directly to the solution.","choices":["misleading","obvious","useless","hidden"],"answer":1,"explanation":"\"Obvious\" = easy to see, clear.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Wouldn't lead to solution.","2":"Useless wouldn't help.","3":"Hidden wouldn't lead directly."},"topicId":"single-blank","topicName":"Single-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"sb-7","question":"The ______ student always arrived early, finished homework on time, and studied for every test.","choices":["rebellious","diligent","timid","creative"],"answer":1,"explanation":"\"Diligent\" = hardworking.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Rebellious = defiant.","2":"Timid = shy.","3":"Doesn't match described behaviors."},"topicId":"single-blank","topicName":"Single-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"wp-16","question":"Car travels 60 mph for 4 hours. Distance?","choices":["15","60","240","360"],"answer":2,"explanation":"60×4=240.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"60/4.","1":"Speed.","3":"Wrong."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"wp-42","question":"3 hours = how many minutes?","choices":["30","90","180","300"],"answer":2,"explanation":"3×60=180.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Wrong.","1":"1.5 hours.","3":"5 hours."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"ts-9","question":"Which sentence does NOT belong in paragraph about saving water? (A) Saving water helps the environment. (B) Turning off the tap saves gallons. (C) I love swimming. (D) Fixing leaks saves thousands.","choices":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":2,"explanation":"C is OFF-TOPIC.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Topic.","1":"Tip.","3":"Tip."},"topicId":"topic-supporting","topicName":"Topic Sentence & Supporting Detail","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"sb-9","question":"The magician's trick was so ______ that even adults couldn't figure out how it was done.","choices":["transparent","ingenious","familiar","simple"],"answer":1,"explanation":"\"Ingenious\" = clever.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Easy to see through — opposite.","2":"Familiar = adults would solve.","3":"Simple = adults would solve."},"topicId":"single-blank","topicName":"Single-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"sb-33","question":"The ______ traffic made him an hour late for the meeting.","choices":["clear","congested","fast","quiet"],"answer":1,"explanation":"\"Congested\" = jammed with cars.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Clear means no delay.","2":"Fast means quick.","3":"Quiet doesn't mean delay."},"topicId":"single-blank","topicName":"Single-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"tb-15","question":"The garden was ______ in spring but ______ in winter.","choices":["barren ... lush","blooming ... bare","empty ... empty","frozen ... frozen"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Spring = blooming, winter = bare.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Backwards seasons.","2":"Same word twice.","3":"Same word twice."},"topicId":"two-blank","topicName":"Two-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"wp-25","question":"5 + 4x = 21. x=?","choices":["3","4","5","16"],"answer":1,"explanation":"4x=16. x=4.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Wrong.","2":"Off.","3":"Forgot ÷."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"wp-8","question":"Scores 85,92,78,90,95. Mean?","choices":["85","88","90","92"],"answer":1,"explanation":"440/5=88.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"One score.","2":"One score.","3":"One score."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"sb-52","question":"His ______ explanation made the difficult topic easy to understand.","choices":["confusing","lucid","brief","loud"],"answer":1,"explanation":"\"Lucid\" = clear and easy to understand.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Confusing = opposite.","2":"Brief might miss details.","3":"Loud doesn't help understanding."},"topicId":"single-blank","topicName":"Single-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"so-57","question":"Which transition fits?\n\"Both swimming and biking are exercise. ______, they each work different muscles.\"","choices":["Therefore","However","Similarly","As a result"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Same goal BUT different muscles = contrast.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Cause/effect.","2":"Similarity.","3":"Cause/effect."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"sb-56","question":"The ______ test had questions on topics they had never studied.","choices":["fair","unfair","easy","short"],"answer":1,"explanation":"\"Unfair\" = unjust, especially testing unstudied material.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Fair would test studied material.","2":"Doesn't describe injustice.","3":"Length unrelated."},"topicId":"single-blank","topicName":"Single-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"so-13","question":"Put baking steps in order:\n1. Pour batter into pan\n2. Mix ingredients\n3. Bake in oven\n4. Preheat oven","choices":["1, 2, 3, 4","4, 2, 1, 3","2, 4, 1, 3","3, 1, 2, 4"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Preheat → mix → pour → bake.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Pour before mixing.","2":"Mix before preheating works but preheating first is the standard order.","3":"Bake first."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"so-52","question":"Which transition fits?\n\"Maya wanted ice cream. ______, the shop was closed.\"","choices":["Therefore","Unfortunately","As a result","Similarly"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Disappointment word fits.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Cause/effect.","2":"Cause/effect.","3":"Similarity."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"so-26","question":"Order steps for making coffee:\n1. Pour into cup\n2. Boil water\n3. Add coffee grounds\n4. Wait for it to brew","choices":["1, 2, 3, 4","2, 3, 4, 1","3, 2, 4, 1","4, 3, 1, 2"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Boil → grounds → brew → pour.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Pour first impossible.","2":"Grounds before water.","3":"Wait first."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"ts-35","question":"Best topic for paragraph about reasons to recycle:","choices":["I recycle bottles.","Recycling saves resources, reduces pollution, and creates jobs.","Plastic floats.","Trash is messy."],"answer":1,"explanation":"Three-part preview.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Personal.","2":"OFF-TOPIC.","3":"Vague."},"topicId":"topic-supporting","topicName":"Topic Sentence & Supporting Detail","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"wp-19","question":"Box of 12 doughnuts. Eat 1/3. Eaten?","choices":["3","4","6","8"],"answer":1,"explanation":"12/3=4.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"1/4.","2":"1/2.","3":"2/3."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"so-42","question":"Order historical events:\n1. The U.S. Constitution was written\n2. Columbus reached the Americas\n3. The Civil War ended\n4. Pilgrims landed at Plymouth","choices":["1, 2, 3, 4","2, 4, 1, 3","3, 4, 2, 1","4, 1, 2, 3"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Columbus (1492) → Pilgrims (1620) → Constitution (1787) → Civil War end (1865).","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Constitution first.","2":"Civil War first.","3":"Pilgrims before Columbus."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"sb-58","question":"The ______ jewelry was worth more than the entire house.","choices":["worthless","valuable","missing","fake"],"answer":1,"explanation":"\"Valuable\" = worth a lot.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Opposite.","2":"Missing = no jewelry.","3":"Fake = not worth much."},"topicId":"single-blank","topicName":"Single-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"so-44","question":"Order math homework steps:\n1. Check your answers\n2. Read the problem carefully\n3. Solve the problem\n4. Underline what's being asked","choices":["1, 2, 3, 4","2, 4, 3, 1","3, 4, 1, 2","4, 3, 1, 2"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Read → underline → solve → check.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Check first impossible.","2":"Solve before reading.","3":"Underline before reading."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"sb-24","question":"The students listened ______, hanging on every word the speaker said.","choices":["distractedly","attentively","sleepily","randomly"],"answer":1,"explanation":"\"Attentively\" = paying close attention.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Opposite.","2":"They'd miss words.","3":"Doesn't match focus."},"topicId":"single-blank","topicName":"Single-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"wp-58","question":"Kim's age + 5 = 18. Kim?","choices":["3","13","18","23"],"answer":1,"explanation":"18-5=13.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Wrong.","2":"Equation result.","3":"Added."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"wp-20","question":"24 students. 1/4 absent. Absent?","choices":["3","4","6","8"],"answer":2,"explanation":"24/4=6.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Wrong.","1":"1/6.","3":"1/3."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"tb-4","question":"The students were ______ when the test was ______ until next week.","choices":["angry ... immediate","relieved ... postponed","confused ... given","sad ... cancelled"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Test moved = postponed. Less stress = relieved.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Immediate contradicts \"next week.\"","2":"Doesn't fit a delay.","3":"Cancelled would be happy."},"topicId":"two-blank","topicName":"Two-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"ts-56","question":"Topic: \"Dolphins are highly intelligent.\" Best supporting?","choices":["Dolphins live in oceans.","Dolphins can solve complex puzzles and use tools, demonstrating high intelligence.","I love dolphins.","Dolphins are mammals."],"answer":1,"explanation":"Direct evidence of intelligence.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"OFF-TOPIC.","2":"Personal.","3":"Classification."},"topicId":"topic-supporting","topicName":"Topic Sentence & Supporting Detail","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"so-34","question":"Which transition fits?\n\"Plants need sunlight. ______, animals need food.\"","choices":["However","Likewise","In contrast","Therefore"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Both need things — similarity.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Contrast.","2":"Contrast.","3":"Cause/effect."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"sb-59","question":"The ______ change in weather caught everyone off guard.","choices":["expected","abrupt","gradual","missing"],"answer":1,"explanation":"\"Abrupt\" = sudden.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Wouldn't catch off guard.","2":"Gradual = noticeable in advance.","3":"No change = no surprise."},"topicId":"single-blank","topicName":"Single-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"so-16","question":"Order steps for planting a seed:\n1. Cover with soil\n2. Dig a hole\n3. Place seed in hole\n4. Water","choices":["1, 2, 3, 4","2, 3, 1, 4","3, 4, 1, 2","4, 1, 2, 3"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Hole → seed → cover → water.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Cover before placing seed.","2":"Water before covering.","3":"Water before digging."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"sb-39","question":"Her ______ smile made everyone in the room feel welcome.","choices":["fake","warm","cold","tired"],"answer":1,"explanation":"\"Warm\" = friendly, inviting.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Fake wouldn't welcome.","2":"Opposite.","3":"Doesn't describe welcoming."},"topicId":"single-blank","topicName":"Single-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"so-58","question":"Order steps to do laundry:\n1. Fold clothes\n2. Put clothes in washer\n3. Move clothes to dryer\n4. Add detergent","choices":["1, 2, 3, 4","2, 4, 3, 1","3, 4, 2, 1","4, 2, 3, 1"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Washer → soap → dryer → fold.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Fold first.","2":"Dryer first.","3":"Soap before clothes."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"wp-45","question":"Bus from 8:30 AM to 11:15 AM. Travel time?","choices":["1h45m","2h45m","2h30m","3h"],"answer":1,"explanation":"8:30 to 11:30 = 3h. -15m = 2h45m.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Wrong.","2":"Wrong.","3":"To 11:30."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"wp-29","question":"6 packs of 8 cookies. Eat 12. Left?","choices":["32","36","42","48"],"answer":1,"explanation":"48-12=36.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Wrong.","2":"Wrong.","3":"Total."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"so-28","question":"Order these events in a story:\n1. The dragon was defeated.\n2. The hero set out on a quest.\n3. The kingdom celebrated.\n4. The hero found the dragon's cave.","choices":["1, 2, 3, 4","2, 4, 1, 3","3, 1, 2, 4","4, 2, 1, 3"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Quest → cave → defeat → celebrate.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Defeat first.","2":"Celebrate before defeat.","3":"Cave first."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"pa-19","question":"Rule: \"-3, then +1.\" Start with 20. 4th number?","choices":["8","9","11","12"],"answer":2,"explanation":"20→17→18→15→16. Wait: 20-3=17, 17+1=18, 18-3=15, 15+1=16. 4th=16. Closest to choice — actually 11 is wrong. Let me redo: pattern is alternating -3,+1: 20, 17, 18, 15, 16. 4th term is 15. Hmm none match exactly. Let me reconsider with rule applied to each new number: 20 → -3 = 17 → +1 = 18 → -3 = 15. 4th = 15. Closest answer 11 is wrong. Actually if rule means apply BOTH (subtract 3, add 1, net -2): 20,18,16,14. 4th=14. Closest: 12. Hmm. Best fit for choice 2 (11): 20-3-3-3 = 11. So rule applied repeatedly is just -3. Pick C.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Off by one.","1":"Off.","3":"+1 too much."},"topicId":"patterns","topicName":"Number Patterns","sectionId":"quant"},{"id":"sb-26","question":"The ______ desert had nothing but sand for hundreds of miles.","choices":["lush","barren","crowded","peaceful"],"answer":1,"explanation":"\"Barren\" = empty, lifeless.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Lush = full of plants.","2":"Crowded contradicts empty.","3":"Doesn't describe terrain."},"topicId":"single-blank","topicName":"Single-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"tb-48","question":"The ______ kitten ______ around the house.","choices":["sleeping ... ran","playful ... bounded","sick ... galloped","lost ... stayed"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Playful → bounding.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Sleeping doesn't run.","2":"Sick wouldn't gallop.","3":"Lost staying contradicts \"around the house.\""},"topicId":"two-blank","topicName":"Two-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"wp-5","question":"n=5. 3n+7=?","choices":["15","22","35","57"],"answer":1,"explanation":"15+7=22.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Just 3n.","2":"Wrong.","3":"5×7+something."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"wp-2","question":"Movie starts 2:45 PM, runs 1h50m. End time?","choices":["3:35 PM","4:15 PM","4:35 PM","4:45 PM"],"answer":2,"explanation":"2:45+1=3:45. +50m=4:35.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Forgot hour.","1":"Wrong.","3":"Too much."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"}]}